{
  "Aquatic Ecosystems": "水生态系统",
  "This lesson covers the fundamental measures of center used to analyze and summarize data sets. You'll learn how to calculate and apply the mean, median, and mode, and understand when each is most appropriate.": "这个课程涵盖了分析和总结数据集的中心的基本测量方法。 您将学会如何计算和应用平均值、 中位数和模式, 并了解何时最合适 。",
  "What is commensalism?": "什么是共产主义?",
  "Commensalism is one of three main types of symbiosis (close, long-term biological interactions). In commensalism, the commensal organism benefits (through shelter, transport, or food) while the host organism is unaffected. Examples include barnacles attaching to whale skin (barnacles gain transport, the whale is unaffected) and epiphytic plants growing on tree branches (gaining access to sunlight without harming the tree).": "共产主义是三种主要的共生关系(近距离、长期生物相互作用)之一。 在共生主义中,共生生物(通过掩蔽、运输或食物)的利益(通过掩蔽、运输或食物)在宿主有机体不受影响的情况下产生。 例子包括挂在鲸鱼皮上的谷仓(护栏运输,鲸鱼不受影响)和树枝上生长的附着植物(在不伤害树的情形下争取阳光的获取 ) 。",
  "What is amensalism?": "什么是美月主义?",
  "Amensalism differs from parasitism and competition because only one species is negatively affected while the other gains no benefit. A classic example is a large tree shading out small ground-cover plants beneath it — the tree is unaffected, but the smaller plants receive less light. Another example is the black walnut tree releasing juglone, a chemical that inhibits the growth of many nearby plants while providing no direct benefit to the walnut tree.": "阿门主义与寄生虫和竞争不同,因为只有一种物种受到不利影响,而另一种物种却无益。 一个典型的例子就是一棵大树遮盖了下面的小型地面覆盖植物 — — 树没有受到影响,但较小的植物得到的光亮较少。 另一个例子是黑核桃树释放的,这是一种抑制附近许多植物生长的化学物质,却对胡桃树没有直接好处。",
  "What is coevolution?": "什么是革命?",
  "Coevolution occurs when changes in one species drive evolutionary changes in another species, and vice versa, creating an ongoing cycle of reciprocal adaptation. This can occur between predators and prey (arms races), parasites and hosts, and mutualists. Classic examples include the coevolution of flowering plants and their pollinators, where flower shape and pollinator anatomy have evolved to match each other.": "当一个物种的变化驱动着另一个物种的进化变化,而另一个物种的进化变化,反之亦然,从而形成一个持续的相互适应循环。 这可能发生在捕食者和猎物(武器竞赛 ) 、 寄生虫和宿主以及相互参与者之间。 典型的例子包括花卉植物及其授粉器的进化,花形和授粉器解剖过程在其中相匹配。",
  "What is mimicry in biology?": "生物学的模仿是什么?",
  "Mimicry is an evolved resemblance between species that provides a selective advantage, typically protection from predators. The two main types are Batesian mimicry (a harmless species resembles a harmful one to deter predators) and Müllerian mimicry (two or more harmful species resemble each other, reinforcing the warning signal). Mimicry demonstrates the power of natural selection to shape physical appearance through predator-prey interactions.": "微生物是一种不同物种的演变相似性,它们提供选择性优势,通常是保护免受掠食动物的侵害。 两种主要类型是贝茨类模仿(无害物种类似于有害物种以威慑捕食者 ) 和 穆勒里类模仿(两个或两个以上有害物种彼此相似,强化了警告信号 ) 。 微生物显示自然选择通过捕食者与捕食动物相互作用塑造外观的自然力量。",
  "What is herbivory?": "什么是草药?",
  "Herbivory is a crucial ecological interaction that transfers energy from primary producers (plants) to primary consumers (herbivores). Herbivores can dramatically affect plant community composition and ecosystem structure. In response, plants have evolved an array of defenses against herbivory, including physical defenses (thorns, tough leaves, bark) and chemical defenses (toxins, tannins, alkaloids), driving coevolutionary arms races.": "草药是将能源从初级生产者(植物)转移到初级消费者(植物)的重要生态互动。 草药可以极大地影响植物群落构成和生态系统结构。 作为回应,植物已经发展出一系列抗草药的防御措施,包括物理防御(长角、硬叶、树皮)和化学防御(毒素、丹宁、藻类 ) , 推动共进军备竞赛。",
  "What is Batesian mimicry?": "Batesian模仿的是什么?",
  "Batesian mimicry, named after naturalist Henry Walter Bates, is an evolutionary strategy where a palatable (harmless) species — the mimic — resembles an unpalatable (harmful, toxic, or dangerous) species — the model. Predators that have learned to avoid the model also avoid the mimic. A classic example is the viceroy butterfly resembling the toxic monarch butterfly. Batesian mimicry only works when the mimic is rarer than the model.": "以自然学家亨利·瓦尔特·贝茨命名的贝茨仿真是一种进化战略,其中一种可口(无害)的物种——模仿物——类似于一种不可喜悦(有害、有毒或危险)的物种——模型。学会避免模型的捕食者也避免了模型的仿真。典型的例子之一是与有毒君主蝴蝶相似的副手蝴蝶。贝茨模仿物只有在仿真物比模型稀有时才起作用。",
  "What is Müllerian mimicry?": "什么是穆列里亚模仿?",
  "Müllerian mimicry, named after Fritz Müller, is a mutually beneficial form of mimicry where two or more unpalatable species share similar warning coloration. Unlike Batesian mimicry (which is parasitic on the model's signal), Müllerian mimicry benefits all species involved because predators learn the shared warning pattern more quickly. Examples include various species of toxic dart frogs sharing similar color patterns, and multiple species of stinging wasps sharing yellow-and-black banding.": "以弗里茨·穆勒(Fritz Müller)命名的Müllerian模仿是一种互利的模仿形式,其中两个或两个以上不受欢迎的物种有着相似的警示颜色。 与贝茨模仿(该模型信号上的寄生虫 ) 不同, 穆勒仿真让所有相关物种都受益,因为捕食者更快地学习共同警示模式。 例子包括不同种类的具有类似颜色模式的有毒达特青蛙,以及多种分享黄黑色带状的叮当黄蜂。",
  "What is aposematic coloration?": "什么是色调?",
  "Aposematic coloration is the opposite of camouflage — instead of hiding, organisms advertise their dangerousness with bright, contrasting colors (often red, orange, yellow combined with black). Predators learn through experience (or innately avoid) these warning signals. Examples include poison dart frogs (bright blue, red, or yellow), coral snakes (red-yellow-black bands), monarch butterflies (orange and black), and ladybugs (red with black spots).": "隐蔽的颜色与伪装相反 — — 而不是隐藏 — — 生物用亮相对比的颜色(通常是红色、橙色、黄色和黑色)来宣传它们的危险性。 捕食者通过经验(或天生的避免)来学习这些警告信号,例如毒达青蛙(赤蓝、红色或黄色)、珊瑚蛇(红黄黑带)、君主蝴蝶(橙色和黑色)和虫(红黑斑)。",
  "What is the difference between obligate and facultative mutualism?": "义务性互助和习惯性互助之间有什么区别?",
  "Obligate mutualism involves partners that are completely dependent on each other for survival — such as fig trees and fig wasps, where each species can only reproduce with the help of the other. Facultative mutualism involves partners that benefit from the relationship but can survive without it — such as plants and their mycorrhizal fungi, where both can survive alone but grow better together. Most mutualisms in nature are facultative.": "义务互助涉及完全依赖彼此生存的伙伴——例如无花果树和无花果黄蜂,其中每种物种只能在他人的帮助下繁殖,具有文化性质的相互协作涉及受益于这种关系但能够在没有这种关系的情况下生存的伙伴——例如植物和它们的鼻血真菌,两者都能够单独生存,但共同成长得更好。",
  "What is allelopathy?": "什么是动脉病?",
  "Allelopathy is a form of chemical warfare in plants — a type of amensalism or competition where one plant releases allelochemicals into the soil, air, or water that suppress the germination, growth, or survival of other plants nearby. The black walnut tree (Juglans nigra) produces juglone, which kills many plant species. Sagebrush (Artemisia) releases volatile terpenes that inhibit neighbors. Allelopathy plays important roles in plant community structure and agricultural weed management.": "蛋白质病是一种植物中的化学战形式——一种美月病或竞争,一种植物将蛋白质化学物释放到土壤、空气或水中,抑制附近其他植物的发芽、生长或生存。黑核桃树(Juglans nigra)生产长松,杀死许多植物物种。Sagebrush(Artemisia)释放挥发性畸形,抑制邻居。 蛋白质病在植物群落结构和农业杂草管理中起着重要作用。",
  "Poison dart frogs (family Dendrobatidae) in Central and South American rainforests display some of the most vivid colors in the animal kingdom — brilliant reds, blues, yellows, oranges, and greens. Their skin contains potent alkaloid toxins (batrachotoxins) derived from their insect diet, which can cause paralysis or death in predators. Indigenous peoples have used these toxins on blowgun darts for hunting. What anti-predator strategy does their coloration represent, and why is it advantageous despite making the frogs highly visible?": "中美洲和南美洲雨林中的毒藤青蛙(Dendrobatidae家庭)展示了动物王国中最生动的颜色——闪亮的红、蓝、黄、橙和绿,它们的皮肤含有因昆虫饮食而形成的可导致食肉动物瘫痪或死亡的强性藻类毒素(巴特拉乔托毒素),土著人民将这些毒素用于猎枪上。 他们的染色策略代表什么? 尽管青蛙非常引人注目,但是它为什么有利呢?",
  "Poison dart frogs are a textbook example of aposematic coloration backed by genuine chemical defense. The bright colors and toxicity are linked: the most toxic species (like Phyllobates terribilis, the golden poison frog — whose skin contains enough batrachotoxin to kill 10 adult humans) tend to be the most brightly colored. Interestingly, captive-raised dart frogs are not toxic because their alkaloid toxins are sequestered from their diet of specific ants and mites. This reveals the diet-dependent nature of their chemical defense, though their aposematic coloration is genetically determined.": "毒镖青蛙是用真正的化学防腐剂支持的外观颜色的典型例子。 光亮的颜色和毒性是相互联系的:最有毒的物种(如金色三里基、金色毒青蛙 — — 其皮肤中含有足以杀死10名成年人类的多巴拉乔托克辛)往往是最亮的颜色。 有趣的是,被俘获的飞镖青蛙并不有毒,因为它们的藻类毒素与特定蚂蚁和蚂蚁的饮食相分离。 这揭示了它们化学防腐的饮食依赖性,尽管它们的外观颜色是由基因决定的。"
}